# Utility script for the org.freedesktop.secrets Secret Service protocol.
# Provides list and lookup operations against the default collection.
# Intended for use by restore-user-before and other shell scripts that need
# to retrieve secrets from KeePassXC at restore time.
#
# For the full diagnostic version (including introspect), see
# docs/dev/kwin_secret_service.py.
#
# COMMANDS
# --------
#   list [--verbose]
#       List all items in the default collection.  Prints label and UserName
#       attribute for each entry, sorted by label.  With --verbose, prints
#       all attributes for each item.  No secrets are fetched.
#
#   lookup <key>
#       Look up the item whose label exactly matches <key> and print its
#       secret to stdout.  <key> is the entry title as shown in KeePassXC.
#
# USAGE
# -----
#   python3 wayland/kwin_secret_service.py list
#   python3 wayland/kwin_secret_service.py list --verbose
#   python3 wayland/kwin_secret_service.py lookup "router-admin"
#
#   # Via the secret-service wrapper (from the project root):
#   secret-service list
#   secret-service lookup "router-admin"
#
# OPTIONS
#   --collection PATH   Override the collection D-Bus path.
#                       Default: /org/freedesktop/secrets/aliases/default
